e%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine%20has%20intensified%20attacks%20on%20Crimea%20in%20recent%20months%20and%20looks%20set%20to%20hit%20the%20Kerch%20Bridge%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20peninsula%2C%20and%20the%20bridge%2C%20are%20crucial%20for%20Russian%20military%20logistics.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Ukrainian%20success%20in%20Crimea%20could%20mark%20the%20end%20of%20the%20war%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20is%20one%20place%20Ukraine%20is%20winning%20in%20the%20war%20against%20Russia%2C%20it's%20Crimea%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%2C%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20battle%20for%20Crimea%20and%20the%20Black%20Sea%20would%20play%20a%20central%20role%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20success%20in%20Crimea%20would%20be%20a%20major%20blow%20for%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia's%20defeat%20in%20Crimea%20would%20be%20not%20just%20a%20defeat%2C%20but%20a%20humiliation%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Olga%20Khvostunova%2C%20a%20fellow%20in%20the%20Eurasia%20Program%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fpri.org%2Farticle%2F2023%2F05%2Fputins-holy-grail-myth-power-and-the-retaking-of-russian-occupied-crimea%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForeign%20Policy%20Research%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202014%2C%20unmarked%20Russian%20forces%2C%20dubbed%20%26quot%3Blittle%20green%20men%2C%26quot%3B%20stormed%20Crimea%2C%20taking%20control%20of%20key%20buildings%20and%20raising%20Russian%20flags%20above%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20March%20of%20that%20year%2C%20Russia's%20Federal%20Assembly%20had%20formally%20ratified%20the%20peninsula's%20annexation.%20The%20war%20in%20the%20Donbas%20began%20just%20a%20month%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainians%20have%20since%20referred%20to%20the%20Black%20Sea%20peninsula%20as%20%26quot%3Boccu