ing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20waves%20during%20the%20cyclones.%20The%20river%20embankments%20are%20protected%20as%20their%20roots%20hold%20the%20earth%20in%20place%20and%20prevent%20landslides.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20noticed%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F305137%2Fneelanjan-chakravarty-from-kolkata-builds-homestay-in-sunderbans-west-bengal-travel-vacation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplaces%20in%20the%20Sundarbans%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20less%20vegetation%20bore%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20cyclonic%20winds%2C%20it%20was%20Biswas%20who%20motivated%20the%20locals%20to%20plant%20mangroves.%20A%20decade-and-a-half%20later%2C%20this%20movement%20has%20led%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20eco-warriors%20who%20are%20mostly%20the%20locals.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20their%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FA-Bahini-volunteer-tending-to-a-sapling_11zon-1717769845.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20JSB%20volunteer%20tending%20to%20a%20mangrove%20sapling.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FA-Bahini-volunteer-tending-to-a-sapling_11zon-1717769845.jpg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FA-Bahini-volunteer-tending-to-a-sapling_11zon-1717769845-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FA-Bahini-volunteer-tending-to-a-sapling_11zon-1717769845-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FA-Bahini-volunteer-tending-to-a-sapling_11zon-1717769845-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FA-Bahini-volunteer-tending-to-a-sapling_11zon-1717769845-1536x1152.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FA-Bahini-volunteer-tending-to-a-sapling_11zon-1717769845-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-352446%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20JSB%20volunteer%20tending%20to%20a%20mangrove%20sapling.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHistory%20of%20the%20region%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20landscape%20of%20the%20Sundarbans%20region%20is%20unique%20and%20includes%20many%20water%20channels.%20The%20sea%20has%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20the%20Sundarban%20island%2C%20and%20the%20tides%20shape%20the%20island%E2%80%99s%20physical%20features.%20Cyclone-prone%2C%20it%20receives%20heavy%20rainfall%20and%20is%20low-lying.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intensity%20of%20natural%20calamities%20has%20increased%20in%20recent%20years%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%C2%A0The%20region%20faces%20a%20significant%20threat%20from%20rising%20sea%20levels%20as%20many%20islands%20have%20already%20submerged%20underwater%20or%20are%20on%20the%20verge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sundarbans%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331813%2Fkochi-murukesan-plants-lakhs-of-mangrove-along-kerala-coastline-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emangrove%20forest%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20home%20to%20the%20Royal%20Bengal%20Tiger%20along%20with%20a%20diverse%20range%20of%20mangrove%20species%20like%20the%20Sundari%20(Heritiera%20fomes)%2C%20Gewa%20(Excoecaria%20agallocha)%2C%20Goran%20(Ceriops%20decandra)%2C%20Keora%20(Sonneratia%20apetala)%2C%20Dhundul%20(Xylocarpus%20granatum)%20and%20Kankra%20(Bruguiera%20gymnorhiza).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3Epalli%20%3C%2Fem%3E(villages)%20in%20the%20Sundarbans%20are%20inhabited%20mostly%20by%20the%20scheduled%20caste%20communities%20who%20were%20rehabilitated%20here%20in%201957%20from%20East%20Bengal%20(present-day%20Bangladesh).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20forefathers%20migrated%20from%20Khulna%20in%201952%20and%20after%20moving%20to%20refugee%20camps%20in%20Asansol%2C%20Serampore%20and%20Canning%2C%20we%20were%20settled%20here%20by%20the%20then%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Dr%20Bidhan%20Chandra%20Ray%20in%201957%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Biswas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEach%20family%20was%20given%20a%20land%20measuring%20nine%20%3Cem%3Ebighas%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20as%20families%20grew%2C%20the%20plots%20were%20divided%20and%20distributed%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%2046-year-old%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201280px)%20100vw%2C%201280px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWomen-digging-land_11zon-1717770332.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Women%20digging%20to%20plant%20the%20saplings.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWomen-digging-land_11zon-1717770332.jpg%201280w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWomen-digging-land_11zon-1717770332-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWomen-digging-land_11zon-1717770332-500x333.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWomen-digging-land_11zon-1717770332-768x512.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWomen-digging-land_11zon-1717770332-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-352450%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWomen%20digging%20to%20plant%20the%20saplings.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Biswas%20began%20planting%20mangrove%20saplings%20along%20Bidyadhari%20river%20with%20the%20help%20of%20some%20children%20in%202005%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20homemakers%2C%20disabled%20people%2C%20senior%20citizens%2C%20and%20%E2%80%98tiger%20widows%E2%80%99%20(women%20who%20lost%20their%20husbands%20to%20tiger%20attacks)%20joined%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20over%20the%20years%2C%20this%20band%20of%20people%20became%20the%20JSB%20which%20has%20grown%20to%20include%20more%20than%20200%20homemakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20Sundari%20which%20is%20dominant%20here%20and%20provides%20critical%20habitat%20and%20resources%20for%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20diverse%20flora%20and%20fauna%2C%20including%20serving%20as%20a%20nursery%20ground%20for%20many%20aquatic%20species.%20Its%20leaves%20have%20glands%20that%20can%20excrete%20excess%20salt%2C%20allowing%20the%20tree%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20saline%20environment%20of%20the%20Sundarbans%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Nivash%20Golder%20(36)%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Jharkhali%2C%20Ashrampada%2C%20who%20heads%20a%20group%20of%2050%20women%20of%20the%20JSB.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInterestingly%2C%20it%20is%20adapted%20to%20thrive%20in%20freshwater%20environments%2C%20which%20allows%20them%20to%20dominate%20areas%20with%20lower%20salinity%20levels%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201280px)%20100vw%2C%201280px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWmen-preparing-land_11zon-1717770425.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Women%20preparing%20the%20land%20for%20plantation.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWmen-preparing-land_11zon-1717770425.jpg%201280w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWmen-preparing-land_11zon-1717770425-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWmen-preparing-land_11zon-1717770425-500x333.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2